**Capital** [None](/Itinerant_court), with a 'chief' court at [Aberffraw](/Aberffraw) &#91;8&#93;. A truly practical arrangement for an era when staying in one place was an invitation to be besieged. An itinerant court, while logistically challenging, allowed rulers to maintain a visible presence across their territories, gather resources, and avoid becoming a static target. [Aberffraw](/Aberffraw), on [Anglesey](/Anglesey), served as a symbolic and often actual center of power, representing the ancestral heartland of the dynasty.

